At Riodoce, they still insist on treating the violence of Sinaloa, although they are heartbroken and although the terrain is now even more treacherous.
Without information about the killers, without justice, the meeting has little use to discuss security, Ibarra says.
"It's very stupid to waste my time in this workshop," he says.
“As long as we don’t know the why, we distrust everyone.”
