It is then expected to be available early next year on many more long-distance routes in Germany," a railway spokesman said.
"Comfort check-in" is what the railway calls the devaluation of tickets without a conductor.
In order to be able to use them, however, some prerequisites must be met: You need a smartphone or a tablet.
And you have to have booked an online ticket - which is what most passengers are already doing.
You also have to have bought it via the app of the train, the DB Navigator, which is the most convenient way of booking tickets anyway.
